Robust Rules for Windsurf Cascade (Astro Titan Core Theme)

Use Absolute Aliases for All Imports: Import components, layouts, data, and assets using @layouts, @components, @data, and @assets aliases (e.g., import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro") to ensure consistency and avoid path-related errors.
Enforce Type Safety with as const: Add as const to all static config objects (e.g., heroContent, featuresSection) to ensure literal types for properties like variant, preventing TypeScript errors as seen in es/index.astro.
Enable Strict TypeScript Settings: Configure tsconfig.json with strict: true and include "astro" in compilerOptions.types to catch type errors and support Astro’s TypeScript integration.
Define Typed Component Props: Use TypeScript interfaces in Astro component frontmatter (e.g., interface Props { content: { title: string; button: { variant: "primary" | "secondary" | "whatsapp" } } }) to enforce consistent prop types across Titan Core components.
Restrict Button Variants: Limit variant props in Titan Core components (e.g., Hero, CtaBanner) to theme-supported values ("primary", "secondary", "whatsapp") and validate them in config objects.
Organize and Reuse Data Files: Store reusable content (e.g., featureLists, statsLists, logoLists) in @data and export typed objects, translating content for multilingual pages like es.
Use Titan Core’s Layout Component: Wrap all pages in @layouts/Layout.astro, passing consistent SEO props (title, description) and optional footerCta as shown in en/index.astro.
Optimize Images with Astro: Place images in @assets and use Astro’s <Image /> component or astro:assets for optimized loading, providing mobile-specific images (e.g., backgroundImageMobile) as in heroContent.
Maintain SEO Consistency: Ensure seoTitle and seoDescription are unique, descriptive, and localized for each page (e.g., Spanish in es, English in en).
Provide Descriptive Alt Text: Include meaningful alt text for all images (e.g., image.alt in SplitPanel) to improve accessibility and SEO.
Minimize Inline Styles: Customize Titan Core components via props (e.g., background, padding) instead of inline CSS to maintain theme consistency and avoid overriding styles.
Avoid Duplicated Components: Remove redundant component renders (e.g., duplicate RecentPosts in es/index.astro) to optimize performance and reduce maintenance.
Translate Data for Multilingual Pages: Localize content in @data files (e.g., featureLists.main.features) for es and other locales to ensure consistency across pages.
Restart Dev Environment After Changes: Run npm run dev and restart the IDE TypeScript service (e.g., Ctrl+Shift+P → TypeScript: Restart TS Server in VS Code) to clear caches and detect errors.
Use Astro File Extensions: Create components with .astro extensions (e.g., @components/sections/Hero.astro) and avoid .jsx or .tsx unless integrating other frameworks.
Follow Titan Core Component Structure: Pass structured content objects (e.g., { eyebrow, title, description, button }) to Titan Core components like Hero, Features, and CtaBanner, as shown in both en and es pages.
Verify Static Build: Run astro build to test static site generation and ensure Titan Core components render correctly before deployment.
Organize Pages by Locale: Structure pages in src/pages/en and src/pages/es for multilingual support, using consistent Titan Core components across locales.
Test Responsiveness: Verify Titan Core components (e.g., SplitPanel, Hero) render correctly on mobile and desktop, using props like backgroundImageMobile and padding.
Document Components and Usage: Add comments in .astro files or a README to explain Titan Core component props and custom configurations, especially for complex sections like Features or Stats.
Always compare each content object, component, and prop in es/index.astro directly with en/index.astro to ensure structural and functional parity for the most accurate bilingual implementation.